\f0\fs24 \cf0 The bus pulled out of the capital\'92s northern terminal at dawn, and Lena pressed her forehead against the cold window as the city thinned around her. First the apartment blocks, then the warehouses, then the long flat fields of grain stubble stretching to the horizon.\
\
She had not planned the journey so much as surrendered to it. Three days ago she had packed a single bag. Two days ago she had given notice at the translation office. Yesterday she had stood in the bus station reading the departure board and felt, for the first time in years, that she was doing something irreversible.\
\
The journey north took eleven hours. As the bus climbed, the landscape shifted\'97fields gave way to forest, the sky lowered, the air through the cracked window turned sharp with pine. She watched the kilometer markers flash past and tried to remember the name of every person she had left behind.\
\
By noon, the first grey ridge of the coastal mountains appeared on the horizon, and Lena closed her eyes.}